 parable so far this year.\nN. Y. Cotton\nNet\nOpen High Low Close Ch ge\nOrs. 23 20 2 3 3* 23 17 23 25 07\nDe 2 3.34 23 45 23 34 23 42 05\n046\nMarch 3 32 23 47 2331 n 2 t47*\u25a0 09\nMav Jl .HI 23 47 23 2* 23 47 10\nJuly 27 12 27 7 1 2312 23 31 +.l 3\n[Oft. 22 61 22 22 *2 22 ***-.33\nDe< 22 59 22 65 22 59 h 2279 e 20\n1 047\nMarth 22 49 22 40 n 2267 20\nb Rid n-Nomlna!\nClosing* i nominal i\u2014November 27 74 Jan\nuary 1946 23 34 February. 27 40 April.\n27 47 June 23 74 August. 23 1* Sep\ntemhei 27 01 November 22*2. January\nI 1047, 22 75 February 22 71\nUrges Clarification\nOf U. S. Fiscal Policy\nReduction of Federal Deficits\nSeen as Aid in Halting' Inflation\nBy MEKRYLF. STANLEY Rt'KFYKFR\nInternational New* Narvlet Economic Cuninimtalnr\nReconversion will he facilitated to the extent that harmony\namong groups is stressed. On the other hand, stimulus ot tendencies\ntoward class warfare will add to the maladjustments and disparities,\nwhich should be ironed out.\nInstead of intolerantly passing judgment at this time on other\nmen\u2019s behavior, we should all make an effort to grasp the causes\nof the prevailing restlessness and climate of insecurity.\nIn any circumstances, the sudden stoppage ot war production\nand the diversion of manpower, materials and tools to peacetime\ndemand would require a major operation. The transition is compli-\ncated by the inherently inflation\nary fiscal policies of the federal\ngovernment.\nAlready the combination of wil\nful deficit financing and necessi\ntous wartime deficits are coming\nhome to plague us.\nThe attitude of workers, which\nhas resulted in a flurry of strikes,\nrepresents in part a subconscious\nuncertainty as to the meaning of\nmoney under present and prospec\ntive conditions.\nAs long as the Inflationary\nprocess continues, it cannot be\nargued that such apprehensions\nare entirely fanciful.\nThe entire economic atmosphere\nwould be improved by clarifying\nthe fiscal policy of the govern\nment.\nFAREWELL TO KEYNES\nThis would entail saying fare\nwell to the ideologies of Lord John\nMaynard Keynes, now in Wash\nington on a financial mission. It\nwould also mean turning our back\non the advice given by Keynes\u2019\nAmerican adherents, such as Prof.\nAlvin H. Hansen, Harvard econo\nmist.\nThe time has come to think In\nterms of fundamental factors. The\noccasion is opportune for stopping\ninflation at the source through\ngreatly reducing and then elimi\nnating federal deficits\nDuring the war. while dollars\nwere issued in larger quantities\nthan the supply of'goods and serv\nices available for civilian's, a\nsecond t> j of more realistic\n\u201cmoney\u2019' in the form of ration\ncoupons was issued for scarce\nitems.\nBY FEDERAL l BASE\nThus, for rationed items, such\nas shoes and sugar, the dollar nn\nlonger remained effective purchas\ning jjower unless implemented by\ni the ration coupon. Thus, in a\nsense, by federal ukase the buying\npower of money w-a-* it-mfiornnly\nrestricted.\nAlthough it is desirable to re\nmove the controls promptly, it\nshould be recognized that the po\ntential inflation will get a ehance\nto work when rationing ends.\nThe adjustment might be i>ain\nful, but the current policy of\nstaving off the inevitable is nerve\nwracking. Past inflationary poli\ncies have accordingly created a\ndilemma, which has not yet been\nresolved.\n11V arc pleased to announce\nthe return from the Aimned Services\nof\nC. LEE JONES\nwho has resumed his association\nwith\nBaker, Simonds Co.\n!1132 Buhl Building Detroit 26, Mich\nLOANS\nON MACHINERY EQUIPMENT\nACCOUNTS RECEIVABLE\nFIXTURES\nNew wcrk'ng car tel for recon\npi'ont vers on ava ab e quickly at\n44 \"Ur>on.\" A phore cal can\nOwe Rfprfirntitnt\nTill citdiy c\u00bbil solve ycwr. industrial r o\"ey\nprob'ems in a few hours.\nUNION INVESTMENT CO.\n320 FORT STREET WEST\n\"TraJe d\u2019iJ Indu'try Financing Since 191 9\u201d\nBERRY\nGARAGE DOORS\nOVERHEAD TYPE\nAll-Aluminum Construction No Sagging No Buckling\nOne of the Lightest Yet Strongest Doors on the Market.\nNo Exposed Springs or Weights. Nothing to Get Out of\nOrder. Easy to Hang.\nWHOLESALE DISTRIBUTORS\nSMITH-ORR COMPANY\n14351 W. WARREN OREGON 0700\nCashiers Name\nNatl Officers\nHelen V. McCoy has been\nelected national president by the\nDetroit-Windsor Life Agency\nCashiers\u2019 Association in balloting\nby which the group elected na\ntional officers of the Life Agency\nCashiers\u2019 Association of the\nUnited States and Canada.\nOther national officers named\nwere R M. Lavell, first vice pres\nident: P. E. Clark, second vice\npresident, and Edna P-iddington,\nthird Hid president. Jean Norton\nwas elected secretary: Kay E.\nJackson, assistant secretary, and\nW. G. Fleming, treasurer.\nThose elected directors of the\nnational association were Gertrude\n,A. Deigert, J. G. Stutzke. Robert\nA. Fay and Muriel F. Bell.\nThe officers are to he installed\n|at a dinner meeting Oct. 18 in\nithe Detroit Loland Hotel. Alleen\niDunagan of San Antonio, Tex., re\ntiring president of the national\ngroup, will he present.\nTrend of Sales\nNEV 3 YORK Or! n me New\nI Yiwk Kl<*k K\u00abrh\u00bbrtre frxlay tntiled 770 000\nItiarr*\nBit hnari \u00bbalr* throw inout the 6a?\nOpen to 1 l 00 .3 10 000 \u00bbhare\u00ab\n|ll 00 lo noon 460 000 \u00bbnare*\nHy INawlar IWnaiD\nISwW rttauai mH Our n\u00abM*\n\u201cWhy Oily 3% of In\nvestors seca re prefits\nin the Stock Marker\nt mintu lafwnaal urn wwr k.Na*\n\u00ab4r AtailaMr to Uie I'iMr\nA -mw\u2019 M far lannlart\nHewd WW OUm Sat#-.\n**l mne\u00ab f art* mrw*\nk!towl\u00abo<r- from yr\u00bbir *4l\nmhMT ilnrt maekrt bmk* J mmrr\nr.ad\n\"If 1 Hha4 rr*ar a mm\nha*. \u00bb\u2014r. nxuty a.wmnltof\n4<'k*n bv4t\u00abr off mda;\nSemre y<**ar ropy nrht nnm.\nPin >1 lo thw \"\u00bbd\u201c \u00bbrxf Mod to\nMirketTrend Surrey\nnet r*rk rwanti rxixM.\no*v* A law Aitcrira 14, (alls.","height":"28002","width":"21495"}}
